The Federal Government, in partnership with the Rural Electrification Agency (REA), has inaugurated a 100KWP solar hybrid mini-grid in Eka Awoke community in Ebonyi State.
   
Executed by Cloud Energy, an energy solutions provider, the project is targeted at addressing capacity shortages in Nigeria, especially in that area, which hitherto, was without electricity for a very long time.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .